<h2 id="author-bio">Author Biography</h2>
<p class="small"><a href="#toc">← Back to Table of Contents</a></p>

<p>
  John Wayne Lee is a Returned Peace Corps Volunteer, federal executive, entrepreneur,
  and lifelong student of history and geography. He has served communities at home and
  abroad—from coastal villages in Costa Rica to complex federal projects in the United
  States.
</p>

<p>
  Over the course of his career, John has worked in planning, project management, and
  leadership roles, including years of service with the U.S. General Services
  Administration. His work has involved supporting agencies that shape public life,
  managing facilities and initiatives that affect thousands of people.
</p>

<p>
  John’s curiosity has led him to study and work with geographic information systems,
  data, and technology, reflecting a belief that learning does not end at any particular
  age. His entrepreneurial ventures and ongoing education in software engineering and
  cloud technologies are part of that same commitment to growth.
</p>

<p>
  Guided by a deep respect for his ancestors’ journeys, John approaches his own life as an
  evolving story—one that honors the past while remaining open to new frontiers, whether
  in geography, work, or personal growth.
</p>

